Take away /disc defensive and evasive altogether and just make us mitigate/avoid that well all the time.<br>
<br>
Disciplines on separate timers. <br>
<br>
Dual wielding giving a significant increase to chance to parry.<br>
<br>
Now for the stuff that's never gonna happen:    <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Special attacks such as:<br>
1) Cleave - same refresh as special attacks other melees get - If attack hits it is automatically a crit<br>
2) Improved Cleave - If attack hits it's automatically a crit for maximum crit damage or close to it(I hate hitting for 18 on a crit)<br>
3) Aimed strike - If successful the attack disables the opponent in some way (snare, stat or ac debuff, temporary blindness, etc. If I hit you in the leg with a two handed axe, it's probably gonna slow your run speed a tad)<br>
4) Wounding strike - If successful the attack causes greater than normal damage (crit dmg perhaps) and for a set duration after that causes per tick bleeding damage.(This should be an initial aggro attention getter)<br>
<br>
Ability for all warriors to use a two handed weapon and a shield.<br>
<br>
Ability for large race warriors to dual wield 2 handed weapons that are not size GIANT. (you cant tell me that a fine steel 2h sword wouldn't look like a toothpick in the hands of an ogre)<br>
<br>
<br>
One or two of these could be added to add some flavor to the class as well as helping with things like initial aggro and the like. (somebody hits me and I start spouting blood like a hemophiliac it's damn well gonna get my attention).<br>
<br>
I've seen several good ideas on this topic, these are just a few of mine.<br>
<br>
Beornegar Frostwolf<br>
